Hi Maura,


Anna Stevens is a seasoned clinical development leader with over a decade o=
f experience advancing immunology and rare disease programs from pre-IND th=
rough Phase 3. She combines top-tier scientific training, MD from Harvard M=
edical School and PhD in Biological Engineering from MIT, with hands-on exp=
ertise in early clinical development, translational medicine, and cross-fun=
ctional leadership.



Currently at Amgen, Anna leads early-stage respiratory and rheumatology ass=
ets, overseeing IND strategy, study design, execution, and safety oversight=
 for first-in-human and proof-of-concept studies. Her prior roles at Bristo=
l Myers Squibb, Takeda, Alexion, and Sanofi further demonstrate her experti=
se across immunology, IBD, SLE, and rare diseases, as well as regulatory en=
gagement and global program leadership.



Anna resides in Mystic, CT, with a 10-year-old, and is open to commuting to=
 Massachusetts twice a week for the right opportunity. While she is not act=
ively searching, she was intrigued by the Aditum role and model and is inte=
rested in exploring it further. In terms of compensation, Anna is targeting=
 the low to mid 400=92s to make a move.



Anna Stevens | https://www.linkedin.com/in/anna-stevens-md-phd-541683/

